	<h2><TMPL_VAR NAME="PAGE_TITLE"> Tips</h2>
	<p><strong>LexisNexis Claims Discovery helps you research prior loss histories, identify claims patterns, detect potential fraud and improve claims outcomes.  Through a Name and Address or a VIN search, Claims Discovery will help you quickly determine how a claim should be handled, reducing cycle time and the probability of unnecessary payouts.</strong></p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>Search methods include:</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p><b>VIN only-</b></p>
	<p>Required fields are VIN and Claim #. Providing data in more fields increases the reliability of your search. You must enter information in the required fields.</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p><b>-- OR --</b></p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p><b>Name and Address-</b></p>
	<p>
        Required fields are Claims #, Last Name, First Name, Street Name, City, State & Zip. For optimal results House #, SSN, Driver License #, State, DOB, Phone # & VIN should be populated.
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>Please see the <a style="cursor: help;" href="javascript:void(0);" onClick="open_help('claims_discovery_help.html');"><u><b>Help Page</b></u></a> for much more information on how to best utilize this powerful report.</p>
